column1:
1. Are you currently working as a Quality Assurance (QA) professional in the Sri Lankan IT industry?

(If “No,” you may exit the survey as this study focuses on QA professionals.)
column2: 2. How many years of experience do you have in QA or software testing?
column3: 3.  What is your current job level?
column4: 4.  What type of IT organization do you work in?
column5: 5. Which software development methodology is primarily used in your company?
column6: 6. On average, how many deadlines or release cycles do you handle per month?
column7: 7.  Have you experienced performance pressure or anxiety during work?
column8: Concern Over Mistakes [I feel upset when I make even a small mistake at work.]
column9: Concern Over Mistakes [I tend to dwell on my mistakes for a long time.]
column10: Concern Over Mistakes [I worry about how others will view me if I make a mistake.]
column11: Concern Over Mistakes [Mistakes at work feel like personal failures to me.]
column12: Concern Over Mistakes [I avoid taking risks at work because I fear making errors.]
column13: Self-Oriented Perfectionism  [I set very high standards for myself in my QA tasks.]
column14: Self-Oriented Perfectionism  [I feel that nothing I do is ever good enough.]
column15: Self-Oriented Perfectionism  [I push myself to deliver flawless results, even at the expense of time or energy.]
column16: Self-Oriented Perfectionism  [I feel uncomfortable submitting work unless it’s perfect.]
column17: Self-Oriented Perfectionism  [I find it hard to relax when my work doesn’t meet my expectations.]
column18: Socially Prescribed Perfectionism  [I feel pressure to meet the expectations of others at work.]
column19: Socially Prescribed Perfectionism  [I think my worth depends on how well I perform in my job.]
column20: Socially Prescribed Perfectionism  [I believe others will only accept me if I’m successful at my work.]
column21: Socially Prescribed Perfectionism  [I often feel judged by my team or supervisor.]
column22: Socially Prescribed Perfectionism  [I worry that failing at a task will disappoint my colleagues.]
column23: Doubts About Actions  [I frequently question whether I’ve done my job correctly.]
column24: Doubts About Actions  [I double-check my work repeatedly to ensure it’s error-free.]
column25: Doubts About Actions  [I often feel unsure about the quality of my testing.]
column26: Doubts About Actions  [I need constant reassurance that my work is good enough]
column27: Doubts About Actions  [I find it difficult to feel satisfied after completing a task.]
column28: Fear of Negative Evaluation  [I worry about receiving negative feedback from others.]
column29: Fear of Negative Evaluation  [I become anxious when I know my work will be reviewed.]
column30: Fear of Negative Evaluation  [I fear that others may think I’m not competent.]
column31: Fear of Negative Evaluation  [I avoid asking for help to prevent looking weak or incapable]
column32: Fear of Negative Evaluation  [I feel uneasy during performance reviews or team evaluations]
column33: Fear of Failure [I worry that failing at a task will make others think less of me.]
column34: Fear of Failure [I avoid taking on new tasks at work if there's a chance I might fail.]
column35: Fear of Failure [I feel ashamed when I make mistakes, even minor ones.]

column37: Fear of Failure [I get anxious at work because I fear disappointing my team or manager.]
column38: Workplace Support [I receive adequate support from my team when I am under pressure.]
column39: Workplace Support [My supervisor is approachable and understanding when I face work challenges.]
column40: Workplace Support [My workplace encourages open discussions about mental health and emotional well-being.]
column41: Workplace Support [I feel comfortable seeking help from peers or supervisors when I encounter difficulties.]
column42: Workplace Support [The company culture promotes collaboration and emotional support during high-pressure periods.]
column43: Performance Anxiety [I often worry about making mistakes at work that could lead to serious consequences.]

column45: Performance Anxiety [Fear of missing defects affects my confidence during test execution.]
column46: Performance Anxiety [I experience physical symptoms (e.g., sweating, heart racing etc.) due to work pressure.]
column47: Performance Anxiety [I constantly question whether my work meets the expected quality standards.]
